content_chunks.content: This e-course provides a comprehensive introduction to Product Environmental Life Cycle Assessment (LCA), a systematic approach to evaluating the environmental impacts associated with all stages of a product's life cycle. From raw material extraction to production, distribution, use, and disposal, participants will learn how to identify, measure, and mitigate environmental impacts to promote sustainable design and decision-making. The course introduces the principles and methodologies for life cycle assessment, relevant regulations, and international standards (e.g., ISO 14040 and ISO 14044), as well as related software solutions. The practical part will introduce the OpenLCA software and demonstrate its use through a simplified case study, followed by independent work on modelling a custom product system.

Life cycle assessment technology for comprehensive environmental impact evaluation - this course delivers systematic methodologies for analyzing product environmental impacts across entire lifecycles from raw material extraction through disposal. Technology for environmental assessment includes Product Environmental Life Cycle Assessment frameworks and comprehensive environmental impact evaluation methodologies for sustainable design optimization. The course introduces raw material extraction impact analysis and production environmental analysis techniques for identifying carbon hotspots and mitigation opportunities throughout supply chains. Participants gain expertise in distribution impact assessment protocols and use phase environmental analysis methods for complete lifecycle evaluation and impact category identification. The curriculum covers ISO 14040 standards compliance, ISO 14044 implementation guidelines, and OpenLCA software utilization for professional LCA modeling and analysis. Students develop skills in LCA goal definition processes, product system analysis methodologies, and life cycle flowcharting techniques for systematic environmental assessment. The course prepares professionals to conduct comprehensive LCAs, develop Environmental Product Declarations (EPD), implement environmental allocation methods, and interpret LCA results for sustainable decision-making in product development and manufacturing industries.
